<!-- Purpose: To test the accesskey attribute used with the AREA tag -->

<!-- Expected result: Pressing Alt+accesskey (a...d) should follow the appropriate link. (Mac users use Command.) -->

<title>XHTML Functional -- AREA - ACCESSKEY</title>

</head>

<body>

<p>This AREA element is using the accesskey attribute. Pressing Alt

+ accesskey (a, b, c, or d) should follow the appropriate link.

(Mac users use Control key.) <object data="images/Mountains.jpg"

type="image/jpeg" usemap="#map1"><map id="map1" name="map1">

<area accesskey="A" href="http://www.mozilla.org/"

alt="Visit mozilla.org" shape="rect" coords="0,0,177,112" />

<area accesskey="B" href="http://www.netscape.com/"

alt="Visit netscape.com" shape="rect" coords="178,0,355,112" />

<area accesskey="C" href="http://www.aol.com/" alt="Visit AOL"

shape="rect" coords="0,113,178,223" />

<area accesskey="D" href="http://www.icq.com/"

alt="Visit Mirabilis" shape="rect" coords="178,113,355,223" />

</map></object></p>

</body>

